# 🧮 Python CLI Calculator

## Overview
A lightweight, interactive Command Line Interface (CLI) calculator built in Python. This project serves as a foundational exercise in Python variables, user input handling, and basic arithmetic operations.

## Features
- Performs basic arithmetic (Addition, Subtraction, Multiplication, Division).
- Takes continuous user input via the command line.
- Handles basic edge cases (e.g., preventing application crashes on invalid inputs).

## Concepts Mastered
- Variables and Data Types
- Control Flow (`if / elif / else`)
- Basic Error Handling

## How to Run
1. Open your terminal and navigate to this folder.
2. Run the script using Python:
   python calculator.py
